-- Roche Talks to Illumina Rivals After Failed Bid, Sonntag Reports
-- B y   C a r o l y n   B a n d e l
-- 2012-04-22T19:09:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/roche-talks-to-illumina-rivals-after-failed-bid-sonntag-reports.html
Roche Holding AG (ROG)  is looking for
alternatives after its takeover of Illumina failed,  Der Sonntag 
reported without saying where it got the information.  The Basel, Switzerland-based drugmaker is in talks with the
research centers of three “large” universities that want to
sell their gene-sequencing technologies to Roche, the Aarau,
Switzerland-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carolyn Bandel in Zurich at 
 cbandel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  